-- Airgas, Belo, Constellation Energy, Dick’s: U.S. Equity Preview
-- B y   W h i t n e y   K i s l i n g
-- 2011-01-04T05:00:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-01-03/airgas-belo-constellation-energy-corning-dick-s-u-s-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies may
have unusual moves in U.S. trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.    Airgas Inc . (ARG US): The packaged-gases company said it
bought Conley Gas Ltd., with about $9 million in annual revenue,
and separately two other businesses with $5 million in annual
revenue.    Annaly Capital Management Inc . (NLY US): The New York-based
real estate investment trust said it plans an offering of 75
million shares.    Belo Corp . (BLC US): The Dallas-based owner of 20
television stations said it estimates a loss of as much as $23
million in the first quarter on a just-completed pension plan
split.  Constellation Energy Group Inc. (CEG US): The developer and
operator of electricity generating facilities completed the
acquisition of Boston Generating LLC power plants for $1.1
billion, the companies said.  Corning Inc. (GLW US): The world’s biggest maker of glass
for flat-panel televisions said Peter Volanakis retired as
president and chief operating officer and Chief Executive
Wendell Weeks will be president.  Dick’s Sporting Goods Inc. (DKS US): The Coraopolis,
Pennsylvania-based chain got a “buy” rating in new coverage at
Janney Montgomery Scott LLC.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Whitney Kisling in New York at 
 wkisling@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 